        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The velocity width of GMCs is in the range of 10-30 km/s whereas the velocity
jump between pre- and post-shock velocities is expected to be 5-10 km/s.  A
velocity resolution of 1.4 km/s should be adequate for the detection of the
shock as an average of several GMCs will be made.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>NIR K-band images from the VLT are available with a resolution of 0.4" which
will be used for the comparison between young stellar clusters and GMCs.
The resolution of 0.4" also corresponds to the typical size of GMCs of
50-100pc at a distance of NGC 2997.  The spiral arm will go through the full
field of 1.5 arcmin and CO emission is expected all along it.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>ALMA Science Verification observation of NGC 4321 in CO (1-0) was made with a
beam of 3.5" x 2.5".  Typical GMCs in that image have a flux of 1 Jy/beam km/s.
Assuming an flat distribution the proposed beam of 0.4" x 0.4" yields a beam
ratio of 54.  The expected peak flux of 20 mJy since the ratio of
CO(1-0)/CO(2-1) is close to unity for GMCs.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
